{"title":"fix(remediation): increase mem-load container memory limit to prevent OOMKilled","body":"Root cause: The mem-load container in Deployment/vigil-app is configured to stress 50M of memory but has a memory limit of only 32Mi, causing OOMKilled when the stress process exceeds the limit.

Evidence: Alert KubeContainerOOMKilled firing for deployment vigil-app in namespace default; declared manifest shows mem-load container with resources.limits.memory: 32Mi but command stress --vm-bytes 50M

Fix: Increase mem-load container memory limit from 32Mi to 64Mi to accommodate the 50M stress workload."}
